&lt;p&gt;In your first 12–18 months, you will have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Built and implemented Carrot&#39;s core procurement policies, workflows, and governance model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivered measurable cost savings and efficiency gains across major spend categories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Established a repeatable sourcing

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Carrot: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://c212.net/c/link/?t=0&amp;amp;l=en&amp;amp;o=4420559-1&amp;amp;h=3535232987&amp;amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.carrotfertility.com%2F&amp;amp;a=Carrot+Fertility&quot;&gt;Carrot&lt;/a&gt; is the leading global fertility and family care platform, built on intelligent care orchestration: the right clinical guidance, at the right moment, in the context of each member’s life. More than a thousand multinational employers, health plans, and health systems trust Carrot to support millions of members across 195 countries – from pre-pregnancy through menopause and major life moments in between. Carrot&#39;s comprehensive clinical program delivers industry-leading cost savings for plan sponsors and award-winning experiences and improved outcomes for millions of people worldwide.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Carrot is widely regarded as a defining force in healthcare innovation as a recipient of several top-tier awards, including Fast Company&#39;s &#39;Most Innovative Companies&#39; and CNBC&#39;s &#39;100 Barrier Breaking Startups&#39;. The company is regularly cited by leading global outlets — including The Economist, Bloomberg, The Wall Street Journal, NPR, ABC News, and Harvard Business Review — as a leading voice on digital health, the future of work, and family health. Learn more at &lt;a href=&quot;http://get-carrot.com&quot;&gt;get-carrot.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Interested in Carrot, but don’t see an open position that aligns with your background? Let’s Connect.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;While we may not have an open position now that aligns with your background, we are always looking for good talent and may have future opportunities suited for your skillset&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; and expertise. By connecting with us, we will have access to your resume and application information for future reference, and we will be sure to reach out if something aligns, and to keep you informed about new positions. As always, if you see any opportunities that open up, please also feel free to submit your application to those roles as well!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We love that you want to help us in our mission of making fertility care accessible to all, and we hope to chat with you soon!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Carrot?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carrot has received national and international recognition for its pioneering work, including Fast Company&#39;s Most Innovative Companies and World Changing Ideas, Inc. Power Partners, and Modern Healthcare’s Innovators. Carrot’s global workforce has been acknowledged with several accolades, including Fortune’s Best Workplaces in Healthcare, Great Place to Work, and Age-Friendly Employer certifications. Carrot is regularly featured in media reporting on issues related to the future of work, women in leadership, and healthcare innovation, including MSNBC, The Economist, Bloomberg, The Wall Street Journal, CNBC, National Public Radio, Harvard Business Review, and more. Learn more at carrotfertility.com.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Carrot: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://c212.net/c/link/?t=0&amp;amp;l=en&amp;amp;o=4420559-1&amp;amp;h=3535232987&amp;amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.carrotfertility.com%2F&amp;amp;a=Carrot+Fertility&quot;&gt;Carrot&lt;/a&gt; is the leading global fertility and family care platform, built on intelligent care orchestration: the right clinical guidance, at the right moment, in the context of each member’s life. More than a thousand multinational employers, health plans, and health systems trust Carrot to support millions of members across 195 countries – from pre-pregnancy through menopause and major life moments in between. Carrot&#39;s comprehensive clinical program delivers industry-leading cost savings for plan sponsors and award-winning experiences and improved outcomes for millions of people worldwide.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Carrot is widely regarded as a defining force in healthcare innovation as a recipient of several top-tier awards, including Fast Company&#39;s &#39;Most Innovative Companies&#39; and CNBC&#39;s &#39;100 Barrier Breaking Startups&#39;. The company is regularly cited by leading global outlets — including The Economist, Bloomberg, The Wall Street Journal, NPR, ABC News, and Harvard Business Review — as a leading voice on digital health, the future of work, and family health. Learn more at &lt;a href=&quot;http://get-carrot.com&quot;&gt;get-carrot.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚀&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carrot is building a future AI-native marketing team with a heavy focus on demand generation, and this role is at the center of it. As a &lt;strong&gt;GTM Engineer (Consultant),&lt;/strong&gt; you will be the person who turns marketing strategy into operational leverage by building the agents, workflows, and automation systems that let the team move faster and compound their output over time. This is not a tooling admin role or a prompt-in-a-chat-window position. It’s a builder role for someone who ships real systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The mandate starts with demand generation, but is explicitly built to expand. You&#39;ll lay an agent and data foundation that extends into account-based marketing (ABM) and partner/channel selling, and that other marketing functions (content, PMM, brand) adopt as Carrot becomes an AI-native marketing org.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the intersection of marketing judgment and technical execution. That means designing Clay-based enrichment and signal plays, building agentic workflows in Claude Code and n8n, and connecting them to Carrot’s marketing stack (Marketo, SFDC, Outreach, Gong) in ways that actually stick. The emphasis is on re-runnability and handoff, not one-off scripts that only you can operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report through the Marketing leadership team and work closely with Demand Generation, Sales, and Revenue Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a 6-month consulting position (approximately 30-40 hours per week) with a potential path to full-time for the right person.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Own &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;💼&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and ship agentic marketing workflows using Claude Code, n8n, and Zapier that extend Carrot&#39;s existing agent fleet across demand generation, ABM, and pipeline creation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build reusable enrichment and signal plays that surface high-intent accounts for the sales and marketing teams to act on&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strengthen the lead-to-opportunity data foundation — clean segmentation, fast and reliable routing, and end-to-end funnel traceability — so targeting and measurement hold up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build out a warehouse-native data spin

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Carrot: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://c212.net/c/link/?t=0&amp;amp;l=en&amp;amp;o=4420559-1&amp;amp;h=3535232987&amp;amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.carrotfertility.com%2F&amp;amp;a=Carrot+Fertility&quot;&gt;Carrot&lt;/a&gt; is the leading global fertility and family care platform, built on intelligent care orchestration: the right clinical guidance, at the right moment, in the context of each member’s life. More than a thousand multinational employers, health plans, and health systems trust Carrot to support millions of members across 195 countries – from pre-pregnancy through menopause and major life moments in between. Carrot&#39;s comprehensive clinical program delivers industry-leading cost savings for plan sponsors and award-winning experiences and improved outcomes for millions of people worldwide.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Carrot is widely regarded as a defining force in healthcare innovation as a recipient of several top-tier awards, including Fast Company&#39;s &#39;Most Innovative Companies&#39; and CNBC&#39;s &#39;100 Barrier Breaking Startups&#39;. The company is regularly cited by leading global outlets — including The Economist, Bloomberg, The Wall Street Journal, NPR, ABC News, and Harvard Business Review — as a leading voice on digital health, the future of work, and family health. Learn more at &lt;a href=&quot;http://get-carrot.com&quot;&gt;get-carrot.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚀&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring a Senior Software Engineer who thrives in high-autonomy environments and wants to own meaningful product and platform outcomes from end to end. This is a role for engineers who enjoy operating with urgency, navigating ambiguity, and delivering production-ready solutions without waiting for perfect conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work closely with product, design, and engineering peers to solve complex problems that directly impact Carrot members, customers, and business performance. You’ll also help shape how our organization leverages AI-assisted development to increase speed, quality, and leverage across the engineering function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Own &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;💼&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own high-stakes work as the DRI.&lt;/strong&gt; Take hard or ill-defined problems in your domain, like a product 1-pager, a member pain point, a partner integration, and own them end-to-end. Design, build, ship, monitor, fix, iterate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design for flexibility.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Carrot aims to be flexible to the needs of the market, our customers, and our members. Our engineering practices should reflect this. When you are breaking down a body of work or sequencing changes, you should aim to deliver value incrementally, so that each small change unlocks value for the business and users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Make the technical calls.&lt;/strong&gt; Make speed-vs-durability tradeoffs and live with the consequences. On contested calls, you drive to a decision rather than waiting for one.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operate what you build.&lt;/strong&gt; You&#39;re on the hook for reliability, observability, and incident response in your domain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use AI as leverage.&lt;/strong&gt; You have strong, specific opinions about AI tools and how they best accelerate work. You know when to trust the model and how to push back when you’re unsure. You raise the bar for how the rest of the org uses these tools.&lt;/li&gt;
